## Where It Runs

| Job | Trigger | File |
|---|---|---|
| Timer expiry + failure recording | Vercel Cron every 5 min | `src/lib/cron/timer-expiry.ts` |
| Extension expiry | Bundled with timer expiry | `src/lib/cron/extension-expiry.ts` |
| Timer warning notifications | Bundled with timer expiry | `src/lib/cron/warning-processor.ts` |
| Holiday pause/resume | Vercel Cron daily at 18:00 | `src/lib/cron/holiday-processor.ts` |
| Combined orchestrator | Called by cron routes | `src/lib/cron/index.ts → runAllCronJobs()` |

All cron actions write an `AuditLog` record with `userId = 'SYSTEM'`. Timer expiry processing is idempotent — re-running on an already-expired timer is a no-op.

